        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_0_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If so then I understand your point but on console (basically a different game) they were (pre-nerf) by far the most used weapon in the game.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_0_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>On console it had no competition purely because... They had no recoil (while other HCs were barely controllable) Almost perfect in-air accuracy (while other HCs barely had any) No bloom (which currently make all 140s and 150s extremely inconsistent) Fastest TTK of all HCs (while you needed to time your shots with other HCs to get the three tap which in turn slows down the TTK) All of this (and more) creates a situation where the best players get the easiest gun to use while those who couldnt get LH/NF have to suffer with weapons that are worse in almost every aspect, this lead to the awful pulse rifle meta on console because pulse rifles are in an amazing spot.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_0_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>P.S. I had Luna pre-nerf and to be perfectly honest, it was boring, they required ZERO skill (and dont give me your bullsh*t about how it required precision because they were basically crit magnets with their aim assist + precision frame) youd have to lack thumbs to have a chance at missing, its basically a HC on training wheels.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_0_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I would love to use my god-rolled waking vigil or thorn on console but the act of doing so was literally putting myself at a disadvantage.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_0_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If youre so self-centered that youre only capable of thinking about yourself and crutches then you shouldnt be playing any online PvP games.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_1_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Actium war rig is arc, auto rifles are solar 0/10</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_2_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Markov Chain gt;swashbuckler</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_2_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>1) Markov Chain has both swashbuckler and grave robber in one trait.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_2_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>2) Markov Chain uses the pre-nerf swashbuckler damage values.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_2_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>e.g. Markov Chain5 = around a 65% damage increase while the current swashbuckler 5 = around a 35% damage increase.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_2_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>3) Monte Carlo is sexier than all weapons that roll with swashbuckler (even you Ancient Gospel). ...</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_2_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Thought so.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_2_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>These are PvE numbers, NOT PvP.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_3_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I agree now that I look back on it.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_3_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The only reason I'm actually putting up this post is because lately I've been hearing people say that Monte Carlo is a crappy ad clearing weapon (which I should've stated in the original post).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_4_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>AR's aren't in that bad of a spot right and after the damage dropoff changes to HC's, I'd argue that AR's are in a pretty good spot right now (PvE and PvP).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_4_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Maybe Hi Cal makes the weapon feel better for CC since it staggers the ads.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_5_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The armor that was reskinned was the IB armor from black armory, not season of the drifter IB armor.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Hunters just like to complain, I never use OEM or BTS (I use bubble with antaeus wards/ Synthoceps) and I always get hatemail (hunters 99.9% of the time).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>While I do think OEM offers a bit too much, I don't think it's as broken as people make it out to be, it's just overused.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I do believe that it's not the only option in PvP and you can do well with many other builds.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shoulder charge isn't OP, just irritating.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It has terrible hit registration for the most part (especially the shield bash, I try and suppress supers and I always get killed because the animation locks on, makes the hit sound and does no damage as well as not suppressing them and I respawn with no melee charge).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And I think it offers great a quick short burst movement option which titans sorely lack (this is why hunters are so maneuverable in PvP (dodge, a burst jump and the best purely speed based exotics, stompees gt;dunemarchers).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>For the most part, if you're getting killed by shoulder charge, it's bad positioning on your part, maybe you ADS too much for too long or maybe you don't back peddle enough.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Supers... Yes, bottom tree striker lasts too long, but I think all roaming supers do, even golden gun.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Fists of Havoc is not OP, Trample is.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_9</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Fists of Havoc is actually quite easy to kill (unless they're right next to you, in which case you would die instantly) only once they start chaining kills it becomes problematic.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_10</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If anything, I'd say stormtrance and arc staff are in the OP category because how hard they are to kill with your weapons (blink + range from stormtrance make extremely hard to beat even with supers and as for arc staff... I don't even want to go there, currently they have the most tanking capabilities like spinning and dodging with damage resistance making them almost impossible headshot snipe and the reach, holy Jesus, I've been killed by a swipe when I was three metres above the guy diagonally) and as for other Titan supers, they're pretty good (burning maul is a great shutdown and has excellent tracking but lacks in maneuverability which makes it hard to dodge things at range, even the little twirl feels clunky but I'm fine with that, firstly because IT'S A GIANT HAMMER, and secondly because it's fine if something has a weakness which opens up a window for outplayability [is this even a word]).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_11</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Side note on class abilities, Hunters have the best by far with a fast cooldown, an instant movement that can easily get you out of danger (and not lock you in an animation that leaves you more vulnerable) and hunters have great close quarters jump ability and have the best in-air accuracy in general (which is kind of unfair).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_12</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If barricade and rift had a faster cast time and barricade had more health then things might be more even.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_13</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Lastly, if you think that the knockout/thundercoil combo is OP then firstly: do you even WORMGOD CARESS (I love this build).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_14</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And secondly: things like this makes the game interesting, build-crafting and all, and there are many more, for example the Arc Battery with bottom tree arcstrider and wormhusk/frostees or Gemini Jester with invis or maybe the disorienting blow for ruining your enemy's radar... I think that combos make the game interesting and there should be more builds with their fun/niche uses.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_15</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If their is something thing that annoys me, it's the fact so many people use the same thing over and over again in a game with this many weapons and builds.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_16</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Yes, some are glaringly better than others *cough cough* mountaintop recluse *cough cough*.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_17</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>In regards to Fists of Havoc, I would remove Trample, keep the health Regen, shorten the duration but keep the cost of the of the shoulder charge attack as it is currently, and replace it with juggernaut shield from D1 (you know because code of the juggernaut) but keep it the same way it used to be but no sliding to reset the shield and it goes on a short cooldown once it breaks and melee hits while knockout is active shorten the cooldown (and anything with armor-piercing capabilities should pierce it but with reduced damage, so things like anti-barrier rounds, AP rounds, Thorn etc).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_6_18</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>TL/DR, titans aren't OP, just overused exotic (with a perk too many) and super (that's relatively easy to deal with, just lasts too long).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_7_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Bubble gang here. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_7_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Though people accuse me of using OEM whenever I use defensive strike because of the overshield).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_8_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Anytime man</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_9_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>While I don't like to just disregard people's arguments, most of my friends are hunters and are like broken records going on and on about OEM, BTS and shoulder charge, then when I use something else on them, they complain about that.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_9_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>At these point, as far as they're concerned, slidey shoes are OPband need a mega nerf. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_9_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I was just salty because my friends hate titans and in turn, hate on me for using literally anything).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_10_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I guess I'm the only one who wanted bonus accuracy and handling on his Duke mk.44.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_11_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Hydras are just oversized dishwashers, goblins are portable soap and minotaurs are just the family bundle... The Undying Mind is the ultra premium kitchen cleanser 10,000!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_11_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And we guardians are but mere bugs...</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_12_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Bubble with Synthoceps plus my trusty chaperone.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_12_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I kind of feel sad when I see a kinderguardian walk into my bubble and I have biotic enhancements active (I let them hit me a few times before I evaporate them into void light).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_12_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And another crutch of mine is antaeus wards.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_12_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>While they can be buggy very rarely, they have a high skill gap and require almost perfect timing but once mastered, they can make you tankier than any OEM overshield (they can make shotguns do next to no damage to you!).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_13_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I like the fighting lion (no other weapon in its archetype).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_13_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And with the catalyst I can pretty much pair it with anything (all kinetic shotguns get opening shot, accuracy bump is very noticeable with most precision weapons and grants pretty much all kinetic and heavy weapons the perk quickdraw).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_14_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Truesight lasts around 7 seconds currently, not 3.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_14_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I did test this out.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>While OEM and Trample are OP, why do titans get hate even if they're not even using the two.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I hate OEM as much as the next guy and I use antaeus wards and still get hate for being a Titan (I use them with bubble, revoker and riskrunner) Why was spectral blades damage resistance kept the same while thundercrash's damage resistance was nerfed?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why does Nova Bomb and blade barrage have twice the blast radius as thundercrash?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why does thundercrash do less than half the damage of Nova Bomb, blade barrage and chaos reach?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why do arcstriders and spectral blades get great hit registration but the sentinel melee can barely hit a granny walking slowly across the road?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why does dawnblade get all of the benefits of hammers and is still able to do laps around the map?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why do warlocks get Icarus dash while Twilight Garrison is still not in D2?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why do hunters get the best inherent in-air accuracy?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why does thundercrash pull you down halfway through your super?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_9</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why do warlocks get grenades get grenades that can wipe teams while requiring the aim of a two-year old to do so (I've used it many times, it's not hard)?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_10</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why do hunters get a get outta jail for free card while the other two classes class abilities trap you in an animation that takes forever to cast?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_11</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why does the one-two peregrine combo get nerfed while the lair's handshake one-two combination blow still destroys in PvE (in fairness, it did get nerfed... Barely)?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_12</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why do Titans get hate for simply being a Titan (only Hunters do this)?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_13</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why do Hunters bitch and moan so much?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_14</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I don't want any of those things I mentioned to get nerfed (other than OEM and Trample [but I really want a thundercrash buff]) but I truly believe that all classes have something that gives them an upper hand over the other classes, we don't need another D2 Y1 all over again.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_15</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>P.S. shoulder charge isn't OP, you should just stop hardscoping and position yourself better.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_15_16</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>P.P.S.S. (don't know if that's even a thing) the knockout + thundercoil combo is not OP, like, did you even WORMGOD CARESS!?!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_17_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I main bubble, antaeus wards and fighting with revoker in PvP. Strikers can already get 2 lightning grenades (top tree/armamentarium).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_17_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I get the feeling that you did not read my comment at all.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_17_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Thundercrash is hands down the worst one-and-done supers in the game and it is in every way (it's easy to avoid, easy to shoot out the sky, has the lowest damage of all of them and has a laughable blast radius).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_17_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I honestly think that is one of the easiest supers to kill right now along with bottom tree striker (before they start chaining kills) because often they get hyper aggressive and make a B-line towards you so it's pretty easy to snipe.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_17_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I've heard the argument that thundercrash is weaker because it has more up-time which is just flat-out wrong, Blade barrage has shards and many mod builds that can let you have almost constant up-time, Nova bomb has skull and nezarac's sin (probably butchered the name) and from the depths to further increase it's damage, chaos reach can cancel early, have an exotic that makes you get it back when it's almost full and the ionic traces give small bumbs to your super but stack very quickly to let you pop it constantly, and what does thundercrash have?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_17_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>An Insurmountable Skullfort, which isn't nearly half as useful as the examples I've just mentioned.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_17_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>See the problem?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_17_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If up-time is all it has going for it, it should be at least ten times better than those examples previously mentioned, and once those get that same/better up-time, they still trump thundercrash in damage to the point where it's honestly just sad.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_18_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I absolutely agree with you (I'm a dirty antaeus wards ape) while OEM is an outlier, there are plenty of good exotics on titans, I just want an all-around hit registration buff to Titans specifically the bottom tree sunbreaker melee, sentinel super melee and hammers.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_18_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Thundercrash just needs a damage buff in general.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_18_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>But if anything, I just want bungie to fix antaeus wards so that they don't reflect projectiles back at you.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_19_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Careful everyone!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_19_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Hunter mains got their panties in a knot.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I use them a ton and I have found out a few things about them: 1) They are almost immune to shotguns (amazing!)</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>But they require almost perfect timing.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>2) Fusion rifles can cause problems such as misadventure and occasionally killing and in the killfeed it would say"(insert name) is down".</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I think that this happens because fusion rifles shoot out their bolts in a burst (7 in total).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If you are looking at the person who shot you, the bolts will go in that direction but if you are looking at the floor even slightly, I think games physics think that the shield is in the floor which causes the bolts to hit you.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>2.5) Jtunn and Telesto are extremely easy to reflect.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Blade barrage as well as wardcliff can be reflected quite easily but will often kill you as well.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>3) Graviton Lance almost insta-kills you for some reason.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>4) It can cancel lock-on for some grenades (like the hunter dodge) for example, if some throws a arcbolt grenade in front of you, you can stop it from hitting you by sliding towards the place of impact (the center of the grenade).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_9</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>5) It grants the super energy equivalent of one kill (pre-nerf super energy) just for simply taking damage and this only happens once per charge/Shield because after using the shield it goes on cooldown (reflective vents).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_10</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The super energy gained from the shield is stacked on the super gained by getting a kill, this can make you get your super very quickly.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_11</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>6) This can be used in your super, making you tankier and making your super last longer.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_12</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The reflected damage does not only grant super energy but also extends your super much like Trample on Fists of Havoc.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_13</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>This point in particular took me a while to figure out but I only noticed it in the season of the Drifter when I was using Hammer of Sol and noticed that I was throwing more hammers than usual (7 is the normal amount, I think).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_20_14</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I used these boots in comp when it was Dust Rock Blues at every corner and I almost never lost any shotgun duels.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_21_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Just make it so that bodyshot damage is the same as crit damage, so 19 per body and 19 per crit.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_21_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The lightweight SMG's have a lightning fast crit TTK but are terribly unforgiving, this still keeps the uniqueness of the recluse but keeps it in check.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_21_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>To compensate, give it greatly increased handling, stability and accuracy (even in-air) while Master of Arms is active.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_21_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>There will be people who say "But won't that completely destroy the weapon in PvE!?!".</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_21_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Yes, yes it will but isn't that the goal, to be able to use PvE weapons in PvE, I would love to use Oxygen SR3 (still could use a slight buff) and Loaded Question (actually very good) but more often than not you are looked down upon for not using the most oPtiMaL weapons.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_21_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>This is why I was happy when The Mountaintop was neutered in PvE with the reload changes, let PvP weapons work in PvP and the same goes for PvE weapons BUT!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_21_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>That doesn't mean that you shouldn't be allowed to use those weapons in whatever activity.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_22_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>What's wrong with Titans winning melee battles against hunters?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_22_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Last I checked titans were the resident punchy bois, not hunters.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
