        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_33_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>You can gun them down quite easily and I don't always use shotguns.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_33_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If you really believe that shoulder charge needs to be nerfed then you are one of two things: lack map awareness and scope in too much or you complain about anything that kills you.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_33_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shoulder charge is far from OP and hardly deserves a nerf, look at the stats, the most played titan subclass is striker and for one reason... BTS and maybe thundercrash.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_33_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The other two titan subclasses are among the least played and need a bit of love from Bungie (excluding bubble, I love that super so much and it's probably in the best state that it's ever been in).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_33_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shoulder charge requires far to much setup and commitment to not be a OHKO.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_33_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Don't worry, I don't expect a great response from a thread filled with whiney hunters but I at least hope that you try and use SC before you cry endlessly about it.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_34_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Indeed, my bad.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>*cough cough* arc web *cough cough* But in all seriousness, shoulder charge is pretty easy to avoid (unless you hardscope) and in all honesty I actually only get killed by it like once every three games in quickplay, I run revoker with a freehand mod and synthoceps (and bubble) and all I do is no-scope melee them, this works because you can do this faster than the shoulder charge animation.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And also, imagine how useless shoulder would be if it didn't OHKO.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Seriously, it would be quicker to just double melee someone because of the animation and it would leave you vulnerable to shotguns and pretty much any close range weapon (SMG's, sidearms etc).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Then there is the argument about the tempest strike and how it should OHKO... No.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>No it shouldn't and I'll tell you why (I play all three classes but I have slightly more time on my titan) firstly, it has almost four times the range than that of the shoulder charge.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Secondly, It can pass through and hit multiple targets for full damage.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It can be activated much faster.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And lastly, instead of putting you in the face of danger (like shoulder charge would) but actually launches you into the air away from an enemies line of sight (it has a bit of a learning curve but it can actually be really satisfying tagging multiple opponents for high damage and leaving them confused as to your location).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Now imagine it could OHKO, you see the problem, and also you could have it up constantly with gambler's dodge (btw, the dodge is ten times better than the barricade).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_9</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>This isn't even including the exotics that reduce the cooldown of/improve the dodge.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_10</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>As for arc web.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_11</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It's extremely powerful and has the possibility of wiping teams but requires some timing and placement.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_12</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>You'll start to notice a trend.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_13</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shoulder Charge: high risk, high reward.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_14</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Handheld Supernova: low/no risk, medium reward.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_15</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Arc Web: low risk, high awareness, tremendous rewards.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_16</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Now let's pretend that Tempest Strike was a OHKO No risk, major rewards.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_35_17</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I rest my case.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
