            	<TEXT>To preface, I took a break from Destiny between the end of Season of Dawn and the beginning of Season of the Splicer so I missed the Wards meta in Worthy.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I used Antaeus pretty much nonstop in PvP from Black Armoury onwards and I still used them through the OEM meta (and I was constantly told to take them off by my teammates since they were considered trash tier).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>My loadout was Parcel of Stardust, Fighting Lion, Antaeus Wards (obviously) and bottom tree striker (pre arc week, I used it purely for the extended melee range from Knockout since I couldn't use Synthoceps).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>So my surprise upon returning to see my baby absolutely neutered, destroyed me.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Let's look at what has changed: Now requires 1.5 seconds to charge up.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>No longer grants super energy or prolongs super.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Changed how chip damage pierces the shield.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Now lets look at the issues: By nature, this is a reaction/prediction based exotic with you reacting to a super or predicting a shotgun blast coming your way.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_9</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Now this worked because of 2 things, no charge up and chip damage scaling.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_10</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>But now with that 1.5 second charge up, the reaction element of this exotic has been complete neutered and to those who say "jUsT spRiNT iNTo A waLL 4HeAd" you are probably the type of person who thinks Shoulder Charge is overpowered.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_11</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The Wards had a mechanic to reward you with good damage resist based on your timing, to put it simply: you would take more damage at the beginning of the shield duration than you would towards the end (25% reduction scaling towards 100% at the last few frames) and it was when this aspect of the wards was tweaked when they became absolutely dominant in pvp.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_12</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>They effectively made it so that you had 100% DR throughout the shield duration (and this is busted).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_13</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Preciously, you had to time it perfectly within the last 1/4 of the shield duration (full duration is ~0.49s) so you had to make a read on a read to both deflect a projectile and take no damage.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_14</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Now after the nerf, you have to make a read on a read ON ANOTHER READ since they also partially reverted the chip damage buff (no longer has 100% DR throughout) effectively making the exotic worse than before they buffed it.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_15</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>You have to prep for 1.5s for a shield that lasts ~0.49s with a DR window of ~0.12s, that's a lot of reads.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_16</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>As for the super aspect, it gave you about the same amount of super energy as a normal kill but the lesser known fact was that if you slid in your super and reflected a projectile, it would extend you super a small amount.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_17</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>While this was an added layer of depth, I'm fine with the super gen on reflect aspect being removed however I would be happy is they added the super extension aspect back (when I super extension, I'm talking about a 15th of the bar here so it was slight!).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_18</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And if were to rework it: I would make it work the same way as it did in Opulence but with the super gen on reflect.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_19</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>But add a longer cooldown between shields (you had it every other slide back then) and instead make it have 2.5s cooldown between shields.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_20</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Maybe as an added benefit, during the shielded slide, the slide nerfs were not in effect (no increased flinch, pellet spread and no stability penalty).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_264_21</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>TL/DR: revert them to the state they were in pre-buff when they were considered a meme exotic (so the people that actually enjoyed using a meme exotic can have it back without it feeling like garbage to use or being blatantly overpowered).</TEXT>
