            	<DOCNO>s_1766_484_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>A hunter Shatterdives the Maul and it gets deleted (54% DR.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_484_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>462 x 0.46 = 212.52/super dead) Then it was repeated on Glacial Quake with a hunter diving and Glacial completely tanks it (90% SDR.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_484_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>462 x 0.1 = 46.2/not even a quarter hp lost).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_484_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Same applies to Shiver Strike, Howl of the Storm and Shatterdive (only during the animations).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_485_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>All slides shatter, you only need to sprint for a short duration if you want the long slide.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_485_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>AND IT'S STILL INFERIOR TO SHATTERDIVE!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_486_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Granted, Warlocks don't need Glaciers since they have Stacy, the Stasis Turret.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_486_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Which is very powerful.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Stacy is less of a 6s ability and more of a 3s ability.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It has around 250 hp and can only take bodyshot damage.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The damage is minimal but the slow is substantial.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The slow lasts 4s with Durance (which also increases the duration of Stacy, use Durance).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Slow disables sprint and the second jump.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Slows down strafe speed, reload speed and ability cooldowns while also increasing flinch.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Probably the most powerful part of Stacy is the fact that it can be thrown (affected by fastball).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>So it can be thrown behind your opponents creating an artificial flank which they have to deal with.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If they are shooting Stacy, they aren't shooting you.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_487_9</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It'll probably get nerfed once more people start using it correctly because of how free it is.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_488_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>People call HoIL sticky grenades OP.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_488_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Which can be tanked with 8 resil.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_489_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I would've thought to make it consume on Shuriken on use.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If we nerf Glaciers even a little all we accomplish is nerfing Behemoth and Shadebinder. "</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Keeping Shatterdive useable" is not the play because if Shatterdive is "useable" through the nerfs of Glaciers, that means Cryoclasm is garbage tier.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It's like you didn't see the numbers.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shatterdive is an objectively better Cryoclasm and Touch of Winter amplifies that (what I truly believe is the problem).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Quite frankly, Shatterdive shouldn't even be on Hunters.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>They were designed to be the slow class while Titans were supposed to be the Crystal/Shatter class.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Every part of Behemoth revolves around either Crystals or Shatter AND IT'S STILL WEAK!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shatterdive is 100% overstepping it's boundaries.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_490_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If we have to nerf a globally available grenade because of one class then the grenade is NOT the issue.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_491_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Bungie said so themselves, even in the Void 3.0 TWAB they speak on the concept of verbs to describe each class.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_491_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>For stasis Warlocks are Freeze, Titans are Shatter and Hunters are Slow.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_491_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>That's why Shatterdive is a slap in the face.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_491_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I don't use shotguns, not my style.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_491_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>But almost all Titan supers are melee supers so we're pretty much Shatterdive fodder.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_491_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Void Hunters aren't getting Shatterdive, it'll just be a dive of some sort with some other secondary effect (invis probably).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_492_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>You have achieved nothing by saying this.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_493_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Remember when everyone was worried about Diamond Lance ruining Crucible?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_494_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It's kind of sad that Hunters have a shatter ability.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_494_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Kinda took Behemoths whole identity and "did it better".</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_494_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If Warlocks had one then Behemoth would plummet into uselessness.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_494_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shadebinder doesn't even need one, Stacy is more than powerful enough.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_495_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shiver Strike has been nerfed in speed, distance, knockback, slow effect, hit reg, cast time and gravity is amped to 100 while it's active.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_495_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>At least Penumbral is still a good ability.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_496_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Pretty much all of the stasis melees got hit.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_496_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>My point was that Warlocks always cry about how much they get nerfed when the other classes also get nerfed. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_496_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shiver Strike got hit harder that Penumbral Blast, I'll die on this hill).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_497_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Look at Chaos Accelerant, "charge your grenade for beefed up effects".</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_497_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Now look at Touch of Winter, beefed up grenades for free (I encountered a guy who argued that you have to use the aspect as a trade-off.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_497_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I want to use Ace but I have to equip it smh).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_498_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Yet Shadebinder was still strong after the nerf, usage was down because of post-nerf syndrome.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_499_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>How do we nerf Glaciers without nerfing Behemoth the most.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_499_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Every part of Behemoth revolves around either Crystals or Shatter.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_499_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Sure you can nerf crystal so you can hit Shatterdive but on the flipside, you nerf Howl of the Storm, Glacial Quake, Cryoclasm (objectively worse Shatterdive), Shiver Strike, Tectonic Harvest and Headstone.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_499_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>All of this so we can balance Shatterdive.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_499_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Behemoth is underperforming as it stands with the super being terrible, that class having a complete anti-synergy with itself and the other classes having superior aspects across the board.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_499_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shatterdive gt;Cryoclasm, Glacial/Grim Harvest gt;Tectonic Harvest, Iceflare Bolt gt;Diamond Lance (granted, the lance is bad period) and Howl is good but leaves you without the ability to shatter unless you use Cryoclasm, additionally, Howl activates in your super yet it still only grants a short freeze.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_499_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Behemoth is lacking and does not need further nerfs (and no, the Rime build is not OP.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_499_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It was nerfed/fixed).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_500_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>So Behemoth has one good build and you want to get rid of it.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_500_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The overshield was already nerfed and in it's current state, it's just a worse stag.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It's not free, it costs both your melee and your grenade.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>And only works at full HP.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Before, when it was bugged to negate crit damage, it was used to counter snipers but since the fix, it's just a 100hp overshield that costs two abilities (which can cycle but it requires you to do it in a specific order for better efficiency).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>3 abilities since you needs to use your barricade to shatter the crystals since you can't use Shiver Strike or Cryoclasm.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The output is simply not worth the cost.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>You'll get domed either way.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Why bother when you could simply throw down a Stag healing rift and be significantly tankier.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Additionally, all stasis subs have access to rime and Hunters produce the most overshield per shard, no one is complaining.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>As it stands, Tectonic is the worst of the Harvest abilities due to the pigeonhole nature of it (while the other two are vastly more flexible) with it's only upside being that no enemies are required.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_9</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>By your logic, if the Rime build is overpowered, then the Bottom arc Stag build is the single most overpowered thing in D2 history since "no enemies are required", in fact, you just need to stand next to teammates to get your tanky rift that heals, provides an overshield, grant DR and gifts arc buddies to you and your teammates with no enemies required.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_501_10</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Behemoth needs a buff before anything.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_502_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>At least Dunemarchers are sexier than Stomp-335</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_503_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I'd love to see a Revenant freeze themself.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_505_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Imagine believing that Silence  amp; Squall and Winter's Wrath are worse than Glacial Quake.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_505_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>That's... Just... Objectively wrong.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_506_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>You stole Twighlight Garrison from us...</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_507_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>How did we take flame shield?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_508_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Force Barrier was a Titan ability in D1.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_508_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It got copy-pasted into D2 with Defensive Strike.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_508_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Force Barrier only gave an overshield on melee kill (same as DS) whereas Flame Shield gave an overshield ON HIT!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_508_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Overshields have always been a Titan thing, Warlocks borrowed Flame Shield.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_508_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Just Like they borrowed Twilight Garrison.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_509_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Tell me you don't play Titan without Telling me you don't play Titan.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_510_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The thing I miss the most from D1 Warlock has to be the OG Nothing Manacles and Scatter Grenades.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_510_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>They nerfed Scatter nades in D2 by giving them a wider spread and made them detonate when they collide with each other.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_510_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Nothing Manacles now are a shadow of their former self. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_510_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Granted, they did get nerfed in D1).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_511_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>TG was a pretty fat chest piece, but isn't the Titan Lift a jetpack of sorts?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_511_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>While the Floof is more floofy.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_512_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Don't worry, I've always been more of a Sharpy Sommelier myself.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_512_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Leave the Crayon Connoiseurs to themselves.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_513_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Did you know that if you use NM with top tree charged nade, it actually weakens the nade.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_513_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Less tracking, lower blast radius and lower damage.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_514_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Casually checks competitive and tourney usage rates... Notices that Hunters have had the highest usage across board long before stasis...</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_515_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Meet Glacial Quake</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_516_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Are you implying that FL was OP beforehand?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_517_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Shelling has been nerfed in every way compared in Rise from Iceborne, yet GL was hardly used in Iceborne.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_517_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>LS is better example of blatantly OP.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_518_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Chappy dodging these patch notes be like:</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_519_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>POV: Nergi is happy to see you</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_520_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Sorry for phone quality</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_521_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>You can't do Raging Brachy dirty like that...</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Howl of the Storm buff?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>This is mostly for PvE but there are some things that I hope to be able to test when I have more time.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Quick list: Does howl benefit from the 50% shiver strike damage increase in super?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Does howl benefit from both the melee damage increase and the super damage increase from Synthoceps?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The reason I'm wondering is because with Thermoclastic blooming equipped, you generate an obscene amount of orbs in super with howl (both super and TB orbs, stacks with Power Preservation).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Additionally, Thermoclastic strike works in super to stun overload champs, meaning that it both counts as both a melee and a super attack.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Lastly, the individual crystals summoned by howl deal "melee type" damage in the code since you can shoot a crystal (made by howl) that's close to an overload and get the stun with the shatter damage.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>With these interactions in mind, I was wondering if Glacial Quake could become a top dps super. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_1766_522_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>In a GM I did yesterday, I was able to obliterate the brig by spamming howl into slam much faster than my teammates who were focusing on the other brig with Ghally and hothead).</TEXT>
        </DOC>
